data.73: Est. Next Promo. Ship Date Start
data.74: Estimated Next Promotion Ship Date End
data.92: Spot for Load Date - When carrier is to leave trailer at shipper location to be available for loading
data.93: Spot for Unload Date - When carrier is to leave trailer to be used for storage
data.94: Spot for Storage Date (No Shipment) - When carrier is to leave trailer to be held in storage until required
data.95: Spot for Load Exchange Date (Export) - When carrier is to leave trailer at prearranged location to allow for load exchange
data.BB: Transaction Control Date - The date when a transaction was prepared
data.BC: Publication Date - The date when a document was published
data.BD: Required By - The date when material is required to be on a site available for use
data.BE: Validated - The date when material obligations were verified
data.BF: Pack Date - The date when requested material was packaged
data.BG: Backorder Release Date - The date when backordered material was made available for issue
data.BH: Offered for Delivery - The date when material was offered for delivery by a carrier
data.BI: Inspection - The date when material was inspected
data.BJ: Shelf-Life Expiration - The date when material will become unusable
data.BK: Warranty Expiration - The date when a manufacturer's warranty expires
data.BL: Manufacture - The date when equipment or material was manufactured
data.BM: Contract Physically Completed - Date contractor made final delivery or performed last service
data.BN: Contract Final Payment - Date final payment on contract was made
data.BO: Estimated Contract Completion - Estimated date when contract will be completed
data.BP: Contract Closed - Date contract was administratively completed and closed
data.BQ: Extended Closeout - New date, beyond the required closeout date, when contract is authorized to be closed
data.BR: Date Delivery Commenced - Date that delivery process is initiated
data.BS: Product Receipt Date - Date that receipt takes place
data.BT: Acceptance - Date material delivery is accepted
data.BU: Rejection - Date that rejection action takes place
data.BV: Recorded - Date action is recorded against accountable records
data.BW: Signature - The date on which a document (e.g., a contract) was signed
data.BX: Action - The date when next required action is to be completed
data.BY: Expected Reply - The date when response may be expected
data.BZ: Demand Receipt Date - Date of receipt of the demand document as recorded in that document by the initial recipient in the supply distribution system
data.CA: Cutoff Date - The date defining the last day of record for the current processing cycle
data.CB: Beginning Date of Customer Plant Shutdown
data.CE: Ending Date of Customer Plant Shutdown
data.KA: Scheduled Service Completion - The date on which a service is scheduled to be completed
data.LA: Last Acquisition - The date of the last acquisition for production services
data.LD: Last Demand - The date when the last request for material was recorded
data.SE: Date Shipped to Port of Embarkation (POE)
